headline: Nvidia and tech stocks lead Wall Street higher
summary: Nvidia is helping to lead the U.S. stock market higher on Wednesday, ahead of the chip company's highly anticipated profit report coming after trading ends for the day.  The S&P 500 rose 0.7% and recovered its losses from earlier in the week, when stocks swung sharply as investors tried to separate potential losers from winners in the artificial-intelligence boom.  Nvidia was the strongest single force lifting the market, and it climbed 2.3%.
